name: src/APIFunc.js
request
description: request() Executes the public API's request. With the Data and URL it calls for the sendAndFollow method.

params.name: data
params.description: Data to send along with the request

name: sendAndFollow
description:
sendAndFollow() executes the public API's request. With the params passed from request(), it hits the API to get a response.
It parses the object data with the help of parseRequest() and parseResponse() data.

params.name: method
params.description: The HTTP method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)

params.name: data
params.description: Data to send along with the request

name: parseRequest
description: parseRequest() parses the public API's request. It stringifies the object data.

name: sendRequest
description: sendRequest() executes the public API's request and returns the response.

params.name: method
params.description: The HTTP method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)

params.name: requestData
params.description: Data to send along with the request

name: parseResponse
description: parseResponse() is for parsing the response received from the request.

return.description: Parses the public API's response and constructs error messages

DateOfBirth

Flight

name: src/LegClass.js
Leg
description: A leg is the smallest unit of travel, in the case of a flight a takeoff immediately followed by a landing at two set points on a particular carrier with a particular flight number.

params.name: aircraft
params.description: Aircraft is flying between an origin and destination.

params.name: arrival
params.description: Flight arrival date in Jodatime format

params.name: departure
params.description: Flight departure date in Jodatime format

params.name: operatingDisclosure
params.description: Department of Transportation disclosure information on the actual operator of a flight in a code share.

params.name: changePlane
params.description: Whether the passenger(s) have to change planes following this leg. Only applies to the next leg.

params.name: data
params.description: [OPTIONAL] any client specific key-value pair specific to leg

name: src/PassengerCountClass.js
PassengerCount
description:
Passenger count - stores the count of passengers, categorizing them under the head of Infant, Child,
adult or senior citizen.

params.name: infantInLap
params.description: Count of infant in lap passengers

params.name: infantInSeat
params.description: Count of infant in seat passengers

PersonDetails
description: Person Details - saves the basic details about the passenger.

params.name: dateOfBirth
params.description: Date Of Birth of the passenger

params.name: isDeciderToPay
params.description: Is he the decider to pay?

name: src/PurchaseDataClass.js
PurchaseData
description:
Purchase Data Class - comprising of the Pricing ID from Pricing API and Trip Data(having trip ID and userInfo) from TripData Class,
returning us the Purchase object

params.name: priceRequestId
params.description: This is the pricing ID , received from the pricing API

params.name: clientNonce
params.description: ClientNonce can be GOLD, PREMIUM or PLATINUM

params.name: tripData
params.description: This is received from the TripData class

params.name: data
params.description: Data having payment related details of the purchased transaction

name: src/SegmentClass.js
Segment
description: A segment is one or more consecutive legs on the same flight.The segment(s) constituting the slice.

params.name: bookingCode
params.description: The booking code or class for this segment.

params.name: bookingCodeCount
params.description: The number of seats available in this booking code on this segment.

params.name: data
params.description: [OPTIONAL] any client specific key-value pair specific to segment

params.name: leg
params.description: Leg object comprising of the details about the hop taken by a flight.Segment can have multiple legs

name: src/SliceClass.js
Slice
description:
A slice represents a traveller's intent, the portion of a low-fare search corresponding to a traveler's request to get between two points. One-way journeys are generally expressed using 1 slice, round-trips using 2.
The slices make up a trip's itinerary.

params.name: duration
params.description: Flight duration (to reach from source to the destination)

params.name: segment
params.description: Segment object having flight data. Slice can have multiple segments

name: src/TripClass.js
Trip
description: Trip Class - comprises of the Flight duration and Array of Slice object

params.name: passengerCounts
params.description: Passenger count object having the total count of travelling passengers.

params.name: data
params.description: [OPTIONAL] any client specific key-value pair specific to trip.

params.name: slices
params.description: Slice object having trip info. Trip can have multiple slices.

name: src/TripDataClass.js
TripData
description:
Trip Data Class - comprising of the Trip ID from Pricing API and Person Details from PersonDetails Class,
returns us the Trip data for Purchase object

params.name: id
params.description: Trip ID received from the Pricing API

params.name: personInfo
params.description: Person details received from PersonDetails Class

/**
 * Created by priyanka on 22/4/16.
 */
/**
 * fBird is another global object including various calls like GET and POST calls.
 * @typedef {Object} fBird
 */

/**
 * fBird.get takes the auth Token and does the authentication for the user.
 * @typedef  { } fBird.get Execute a GET request.
 * @property {string} path To the requested resource
 * @property {object} [params] Object of additional parameters
 */

/**
 * fBird.post returns with a request call on the pricing endpoint.
 * @typedef  { } fBird.post Execute a PUT request.
 * @property {string} path To the requested resource
 * @property {object} [params] Object of additional parameters
 */

/**
 * XMLHttpRequest is a global object with a Fake XMLHttpRequest function ( useFakeXMLHttpRequest() ) to run the SDK test cases.
 * @typedef {Object} XMLHttpRequest
 */
